Student Management (Flask + MySQL) - Quick Start
------------------------------------------------

1) Create MySQL database & table:
   - Open MySQL and run:
     CREATE DATABASE student_db;
     USE student_db;
     CREATE TABLE students (
       id INT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
       name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
       age INT NOT NULL,
       grade VARCHAR(10) NOT NULL
     );

2) Update db.py:
   - Set your MySQL user/password if different from defaults.

3) Install Python deps:
   pip install -r requirements.txt

4) Run the app:
   python app.py
   Open http://127.0.0.1:5000

5) Notes:
   - Theme is persisted in localStorage.
   - Uses Feather icons (loaded from CDN).
   - Frontend uses fetch() to talk to the Flask API endpoints.
